    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with **Josh Lowe** (70.92) and **Heliot Ramos** (67.76) leading the charge as our most viable offensive anchors. **Josh Lowe** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Davis Martin, with a +14% boost from a dynamic platoon edge and a +5% wind-out factor that pushes his ceiling into the elite tier. Similarly, **Heliot Ramos** capitalizes on a high-upside matchup against Randy V\u00e1squez; his score is buoyed by a substantial +19% SP skill advantage, making him a high-efficiency play despite a slight park penalty. **Gunnar Henderson** remains a must-start at 67.58, as his dynamic platoon advantage against Schlittler compensates for the opposing pitcher's moderate baseline, keeping our SS production firmly in the strong category.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involves the benching of **Coby Mayo**, whose 40.71 score narrowly missed the cut behind the stability of our current utility options. While **Coby Mayo** benefits from the same park factors as **Gunnar Henderson**, his score was dragged down by a -8% platoon drag and an optimizer preference for the higher floors offered by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.07) and **Sam Antonacci** (58.18). **Sam Antonacci** earns his start via the top-of-the-order boost (+10%) and an excellent .400 xwOBA profile against Jos\u00e9 Soriano, making him our preferred play for stolen base upside, a category where we remain acutely aggressive. \n\nWe are monitoring the status of **Drake Baldwin**, **Nolan Schanuel**, and **Miguel Vargas** closely, as the \"Lineup Pending\" designation introduces inherent volatility. **Drake Baldwin** is currently flagged with a -19% SP skill penalty due to Logan Gilbert\u2019s elite profile, rendering his 43.40 score somewhat marginal; if the official lineup drops and he is demoted from the #2 spot, he will be the first candidate for rotation to preserve our game caps. **Kyle Tucker** continues to provide steady 